15/01/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- During a visit to Zagreb Tuesday (14 January), Greek Foreign Minister Georges Papandreou vowed to support Croatia's EU accession efforts and congratulated state authorities for successfully implementing economic and political reforms.
At a joint press conference with Croatian Prime Minister Ivica Racan, Papandreou said the Greek presidency of the EU would encourage Croatia to finalise the Stabilisation and Association Agreement and to launch official negotiations for EU entry.
He suggested 2007 as a possible date if the country speeds up reforms.
Racan confirmed plans to submit an application to launch accession talks in February.
(Vecernji List, Vjesnik - 15/01/03;
HINA, HRT, AP, AFP - 14/01/03)
